The Kenya National Union of Nurses wants Salaries and Remuneration Commission chairperson Sarah Serem to resign over a "shoddy" job evaluation report.Seth Panyako, Union Secretary General said the SRC used billions of shillings to carry out job evaluation only to duplicate existence documents.The commission on Friday released a new job structure for over 600,000 public servants seeking to bridge the gap between the highest and lowest pay earners.Panyako accused the commission Chair of duplicating jobs in the newly released job groups from previous documents. This is total shame and she need to resign for wasting public resources in the pretext of job evaluation exercise, he said.Panyako on Saturday opposed the report saying the union will mobilize nurses to go on strike over what they termed as betrayal by SRC in the job evaluation process.